    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats`\n\n**8 files to touch, 2 are new.**\n\n### What the command will look like\n\n```\n$ uv cache stats --preview\nwheels                0\nsource-distributions  0\nflat-index            0\ngit                   0\ninterpreter           0\nsimple                0\narchive               0\nbuilds                0\nenvironments          0\nbinaries              0\ntotal                 0\n\n$ uv cache stats --preview --human\nwheels                117.7 MiB\nsource-distributions   22.4 MiB\n...\ntotal                 190.6 MiB\n```\n\n### The 8 changes\n\n| # | File | What |\n|---|------|------|\n| 1 | `crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs` | Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` variant + `as_str` + `FromStr` arms |\n| 2 | `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct |\n| 3 | `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | **New** – core implementation: iterates `CacheBucket::iter()`, measures each via `diskus::DiskUsage`, prints aligned table with total |\n| 4 | `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | Add `mod cache_stats` + re-export |\n| 5 | `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` |\n| 6 | `crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs` | Add `cache_stats()` command helper + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter |\n| 7 | `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs` | **New** – 3 integration tests (empty raw, populated raw, populated human) |\n| 8 | `crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs` | Register `mod cache_stats` under `test-python + test-pypi` feature gate |\n\n**Key reuses:** `diskus::DiskUsage` (same as `cache_size`), `human_readable_bytes` from `uv_console`, `CacheBucket::iter()` + `cache.bucket()` for paths, `PreviewFeature` gating pattern identical to `CacheSize`.",
